---
import Card from "@components/containers/Card.astro";
import Grid from "@components/containers/Grid.astro";
import Lyrics from "@icons/lyrics.svg";
import Code from "@icons/code.svg";
import Bolt from "@icons/bolt.svg";
import Design from "@icons/design.svg";
import Paintbrush from "@icons/paintbrush.svg";
import Widgets from "@icons/widgets.svg";
---

<Grid>
	<Card>
		<h4><Design class="icon" />Beautiful Design</h4>
		<p>Navic boasts the Material 3 Expressive design language, which is Google's latest design system.</p>
	</Card>
	<Card>
		<h4><Widgets class="icon" />Widgets</h4>
		<p>Navic features a couple of home screen widgets with a consistent Material design.</p>
	</Card>
	<Card>
		<h4><Lyrics class="icon" />Lyrics</h4>
		<p>Navic supports a couple of lyric providers out of the box and has a beautiful lyrics interface.</p>
	</Card>
	<Card>
		<h4><Bolt class="icon" />Powerful</h4>
		<p>Navic implements most of Subsonic's API, letting you manage and see your library easily, for example, create/modify playlists and shares, and more.</p>
	</Card>
	<Card>
		<h4><Paintbrush class="icon" />Highly customisable</h4>
		<p>Navic has many settings and more to come. Basic theming is also possible.</p>
	</Card>
	<Card>
		<h4><Code class="icon" />Free & open source</h4>
		<p>Navic is free and open source forever, and was originally made in need of an open source Navidrome client.</p>
	</Card>
</Grid>

<style>
	.icon {
		vertical-align: middle;
		margin-right: 7px;
	}
	h4 {
		margin: 0;
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		line-height: 24px !important;
	}
	p {
		margin-top: 5px;
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}
</style>
